WEBVTT

00:00.423 --> 00:03.739
The dark web, however, is not just an eBay for illegal purchases.

00:03.957 --> 00:08.210
It's also used by radical extremists to communicate and spread propaganda,...

00:08.567 --> 00:12.480
...but not all activity going on down in the dark web is illegal.

00:13.265 --> 00:16.373
TOR, for instance, receives 60% of its backing...

00:16.614 --> 00:21.115
...from the US State Department and the Department of Defense to act as a secure network...

00:21.378 --> 00:26.145
...for both government agencies and political dissidents fighting oppressive regimes.

00:26.523 --> 00:29.577
Over the past decade, the dark web has empowered activists...

00:29.771 --> 00:31.889
...to spread news during the Arab Spring...

00:32.061 --> 00:34.612
...and encourage whistle-blowers to release information.

00:35.295 --> 00:40.199
The dark web as a tool to help journalists uncover the truth was made popular by Wikileaks.

00:40.423 --> 00:44.335
Now, news organizations such as The New York Times and The Guardian...

00:44.502 --> 00:50.210
...all host dark web drop sites for uploading anonymously-leaked tips and documents.

00:50.728 --> 00:54.919
It's also helped domestic violence victims hide from online stalkers...

00:55.109 --> 00:57.579
...and allowed ordinary citizens to surf the web...

00:57.689 --> 01:00.797
...without being tracked by advertisers or even the government.

